metadata.name: Meridian #2
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Meridian' attempts to capture some of the beauty and simplicity of Bauhaus design ideas. The addition of a line (or Meridian) to these simple shapes creates a colorful, striking design with an Art Deco vibe!

To download:
Click/tap 'open', then click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x2000px PNG.

metadata.name: auras (scotomas from an auric migraine) #3
metadata.description:
auras (scotomas from an auric migraine)

have you ever had an auric migraine?

i have.

five exactly.

electric storms on my brain stem.

with pretty little floaters to obscure my vision.

this is my attempt to abstractly touch them.

such terrifyingly gorgeous creatures.

here -> you can have one too...

xo, 

shim sham*

*mouse click for a high pitch buzz for the migraine sensitivity to sound effect









origin story
in october 2019 shim sham her first auric migraine attack that included an episode of transient aphasia. known as a basilar or aural brain stem migraine, it creates an electrical storm at the base of the brain stem, which results in visual auras with blind spots (scotomas) sometimes outlined with geometric designs or zigzag lines that slowly float across your vision; shimmering stars. the onset sometimes begins with flashes of light, transient aphasia ~ speech difficulty, and the auric visions, followed by tingling in the hands and face, extreme pain, along with extreme sensitivity to sound and light, before, during and after the migraine. the post drome phase is the aftermath of the brainstorm and can last several days with an overall brain fog, dull headache pain, lethargy and sensitivity to sound and light. 

the aura is due to an electrical or chemical wave that moves across the brain. literally it is a brain storm. 

the auras that shim sham has seen are the most beautiful and terrifying apparitions ever experienced in waking life. in four years she's had 5. each one was different, beautiful and transformative. 

this an attempt at creating a visual and sonic abstraction to share with the world and acknowledge that some of us experience these things, each individually unique and wild.

concept originally inspired by "Depth sorting" by Jakub Valtar from processing 4 examples.

gratitude to joey zaza

made with p5.js and adapted from processing 4.

metadata.name: Transition: Omnidimensional #72
metadata.description:
This piece is a corrupted version of Transition: Multidimensional. The code is nearly identical but there are small changes in decisive places. Small numbers have become big, muted colors have become bright and if/else statements have become if statements.

The instructions for the animations have not been changed, yet they appear vastly different from Transition: Multidimensional. Use with caution. 

— Interactions —

A - Start/stop Animation A (epileptic trigger warning)

B - Start/stop Animation B (epileptic trigger warning)

H - Load in 4x resolution

S - Save as image (only in live view)

— Credits —

Made with p5.js, Typescript and Webpack.

metadata.name: slow draw (rare version) #6
metadata.description:
lines gather into creature esque spots called poofs.

are they urchin?

above them circles are drawn.

drawing circles is essential to creating magic.

moving your mouse may affect the drawing of the circles, casting your energy into the spell.

slow draw (rare version) allows you to gaze, relax and meditate with the sketch and the sound.

watch the circles slowly complete themselves and the sacred geometry emerge. listen, feel, and receive.

it is magic. it is healing.

one mouse click resets it all to begin again.

sound triggers with mouse click. the selected frequencies are 114, 174, 195, 285, 396 Hz to help your subconscious mind and body become free of tension and pain, lower stress, balance your energy for survival, instinct, and safety, help your mind feel free of all guilt, fear, and to relieve anxiety and negative energies.

may you receive what you need.

my deepest gratitude to joey zaza for continuing to inspire me and hold space for my visions.

and thanks to you dear collector for believing in and collecting this magical slow draw (rare version).

♡,

cari ann shim sham*

metadata.name: ⚖ Justice #8
metadata.description:
This work is one of the Nfts that belong to the collection "⚖ Justice"

Technique: Multi-layered generative art processed with Photoshop
Size: 3000 × 2000 px

These generative artworks are conceived with the intention of conveying a social message of denouncing violence and suffering, rebelling against injustices, and defending human rights. Each piece expresses a strong sense of social commitment that goes beyond words and manifests itself through art.

Each work invites reflection on the current state of our society. Justice should be a universal right for every individual, but too often it becomes a matter of money and power.
These artworks speak to the viewer on a visceral level, inviting them to contemplate the injustices in our world and to take action.

metadata.name: System α #149
metadata.description:
"To capture the fleeting time in the generating process."

In this work,I d'like focus on the generating of generative art system itself rather than imitate some scene or style.
And with the flow of time, try to figure out where it can take me toward.

This work would be a series of my alternative view on generative art.
"α" means the first step of this series.

Press [s] in live view to save file as PNG.
Press [p] to stop.

------
Happy first birthday fx(hash) !!

20% of primary revenues go to Savepakistan Flood Relief Fundraiser.
20% of primary revenues go to the Processing foundation.
